<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<catalogue id="b2e4c6d3-0000-4000-8000-000000000001" name="Chaos - Daemonic Incursion" revision="2" battleScribeVersion="2.00" authorName="Black Crusade / Omnihammer project" gameSystemId="a1f3b5c2-0000-4000-8000-000000000001" gameSystemRevision="1" xmlns="http://www.battlescribe.net/schema/catalogueSchema">
  <profiles/>
  <rules/>
  <infoLinks/>
  <costTypes/>
  <profileTypes/>
  <forceEntries>
    <forceEntry id="b2e4c6d3-0000-4000-8000-000000000010" name="Daemonic Incursion Detachment" hidden="false">
      <profiles/>
      <rules>
        <rule id="b2e4c6d3-0000-4000-8000-000000000020" name="Daemonic Incursion Benefit" hidden="false">
          <profiles/>
          <rules/>
          <infoLinks/>
          <modifiers/>
          <description>Units in a Daemonic Incursion Detachment ignore the restrictions of the Daemonic Summoning and Daemonic Possession special rules — they may deploy normally, use standard Reserves, or Deep Strike as their datasheets allow.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="b2e4c6d3-0000-4000-8000-000000000023" name="Daemons in Detachments" hidden="false">
          <profiles/>
          <rules/>
          <infoLinks/>
          <modifiers/>
          <description>For all Detachments that are NOT Daemonic Incursion Detachments, units that contain models with the Daemon, Daemon of Khorne, Daemon of Nurgle, Daemon of Slaanesh, or Daemon of Tzeentch special rules may not be included unless the model has the Daemonic Possession or Daemonic Summoning special rule. If a daemon model does not have one of these rules, it is restricted to Daemonic Incursion Detachments.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="b2e4c6d3-0000-4000-8000-000000000021" name="Daemon of Khorne" hidden="false">
          <profiles/>
          <rules/>
          <infoLinks/>
          <modifiers/>
          <description>A model with this rule is a Daemonic entity of the Blood God. They possess the following Universal Special Rules: Daemon, Furious Charge, Rage, Fleet, Adamantium Will.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="b2e4c6d3-0000-4000-8000-000000000022" name="The Blood God&apos;s Due" hidden="false">
          <profiles/>
          <rules/>
          <infoLinks/>
          <modifiers/>
          <description>In the Assault Phase, if a unit entirely composed of models with this special rule wipes out an enemy unit and performs an Overrun! consolidation, add +1&quot; to the result. If the die roll is a 1, the unit immediately suffers D3 automatic hits resolved at the unit&apos;s majority Strength and AP.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="b2e4c6d3-0000-4000-8000-000000000024" name="The Warp Tide" hidden="false">
          <profiles/>
          <rules/>
          <infoLinks/>
          <modifiers/>
          <description>The daemon player tracks their current Warp Tide level on a counter or die visible to both players. The Warp Tide represents how thoroughly the barrier between realspace and the Immaterium has been compromised. Starting level is 0.

GENERATION:
• Start of each Daemon player turn: +1
• A friendly Daemon unit completely destroys an enemy unit: +1
• A friendly Daemon unit is completely destroyed: +1
• The Daemon Warlord slays an enemy Character in a Heroic Duel: +1

RULES: Warp Tide may never exceed 12. Warp Tide never decreases. Warp Tide is generated immediately when a triggering event occurs.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="b2e4c6d3-0000-4000-8000-000000000025" name="Warp Rift Zones" hidden="false">
          <profiles/>
          <rules/>
          <infoLinks/>
          <modifiers/>
          <description>Each unit composed entirely of models with the Daemon USR in a Daemonic Incursion detachment generates a Warp Rift Zone — an aura extending outward from the unit. The size and intensity scales with the current Warp Tide level:

WARP TIDE 0-2 — 3&quot; zone — Whispers of the Warp: -1 Ld.
WARP TIDE 3-5 — 6&quot; zone — The Veil Thins: -1 Ld, zone counts as Dangerous Terrain for enemy models.
WARP TIDE 6-11 — 6&quot; zone — Reality Fractures: -2 Ld, Dangerous Terrain, enemy units must pass a Leadership Test to use Stand &amp; Shoot! and Return Fire! Reactions. If failed, the reaction is lost (unit does not fire).
WARP TIDE 12 — 9&quot; zone — The Warp Made Manifest: -2 Ld, Dangerous Terrain, Leadership Tests for reactions, and enemy models that start their turn wholly within the Zone suffer a S4 AP- hit.

RULES: Leadership penalties from overlapping Zones do not stack. Dangerous Terrain from Zones is tested when enemy models move through or end their move within the Zone. Models with the Daemon USR are never affected by Warp Rift Zones. The Leadership test for reactions uses the unit&apos;s modified Leadership (after the Zone penalty) and is taken before firing is resolved. The hits from Warp Made Manifest are resolved at the beginning of the enemy player&apos;s turn, before movement.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="b2e4c6d3-0000-4000-8000-000000000026" name="Daemonic Resurgence" hidden="false">
          <profiles/>
          <rules/>
          <infoLinks/>
          <modifiers/>
          <description>At the start of each Daemon player&apos;s Movement Phase, before any units move, perform a Resurgence Check for each friendly daemon unit on the battlefield that has lost models but is not destroyed:

WARP TIDE 0-2 — No Resurgence.
WARP TIDE 3-5 — Model returns on 6+.
WARP TIDE 6-9 — Model returns on 5+.
WARP TIDE 10-12 — Model returns on 4+.

Roll a D6 for each slain model. If the roll meets the threshold, that model is returned to the unit in coherency with surviving models, as close to the unit as possible.

RULES: Returned models count as having moved this turn. They may act normally in subsequent phases (charge, fight in melee, etc.). A model may only be returned via resurgence once per turn. Resurgence is rolled before any other start-of-turn effects.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="b2e4c6d3-0000-4000-8000-000000000027" name="Daemonic Reformation" hidden="false">
          <profiles/>
          <rules/>
          <infoLinks/>
          <modifiers/>
          <description>WARP TIDE 7+ REQUIRED. ONCE PER GAME.

If a friendly daemon unit has been completely destroyed, the daemon player may declare a Daemonic Reformation at the start of their Movement Phase. The destroyed unit is placed in Ongoing Reserves at its minimum starting unit size with default wargear only (no upgrades). It arrives next turn via Deep Strike using the standard Daemonic Summoning placement rules (within 6&quot; of a friendly model with a Personal Icon, no scatter). If no friendly model with a Personal Icon is on the battlefield when it arrives, the unit is destroyed.

RULES: Reformation may only be used once per game regardless of how many units have been destroyed. The reformed unit counts as a new unit with the same profile as the destroyed unit, counts toward the army&apos;s unit count for victory conditions, and benefits from all Daemonic Incursion rules upon arrival.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="b2e4c6d3-0000-4000-8000-000000000028" name="Warp Storm" hidden="false">
          <profiles/>
          <rules/>
          <infoLinks/>
          <modifiers/>
          <description>WARP TIDE 10+ REQUIRED. If your Warlord is in this detachment, at the start of each of your shooting phases, roll 2D6 and apply the Warp Storm result:

2 — THE STORM ABATES: All units with the Daemon special rule (friend or foe) must immediately take a Daemonic Instability Test.
3 — PUNISHED BY THE GODS: Randomly select one character (friend or foe) with the Daemon rule. It takes a Daemonic Instability test on 3D6. Wounds caused can only be allocated to the selected character. If no Daemon characters are on the table, count this as The Warp is Calm.
4 — WARP EBB: All Daemon models suffer -1 to invulnerable saves (min 6+) until the next Warp Storm roll.
5 — STORM OF FIRE: Roll D6 for each unengaged friendly unit containing Daemons of Nurgle (or Mark of Nurgle) and each unengaged enemy unit. On a 6, place a large blast template centred on any model — it scatters. S4 AP5 Barrage, Ignores Cover hits to each unit partially under template.
6 — ROT, GLORIOUS ROT: Roll D6 for each unengaged friendly Daemons of Tzeentch unit (or Mark of Tzeentch) and each unengaged enemy unit. On a 6, that unit suffers D6 S4 AP3 hits with Poisoned (4+) and Ignores Cover. Vehicles hit side armour.
7 — THE WARP IS CALM: Nothing happens.
8 — THE DARK PRINCE THIRSTS: Roll D6 for each unengaged friendly Daemons of Khorne unit (or Mark of Khorne) and each unengaged enemy unit. On a 6, that unit suffers D6 S6 AP- hits with Rending and Ignores Cover. Vehicles hit side armour.
9 — KHORNE&apos;S WRATH: Roll D6 for each unengaged friendly Daemons of Slaanesh unit (or Mark of Slaanesh) and each unengaged enemy unit. On a 6, place a small blast template — it scatters. S8 AP3 Barrage hits to each unit partially under template.
10 — WARP SURGE: All Daemon models gain +1 to invulnerable saves (max 4+) until the next Warp Storm roll.
11 — DAEMONIC POSSESSION: Randomly select one non-vehicle enemy Psyker without the Daemon rule. The Psyker must pass Ld on 3D6 or be removed (no saves). On failure, place a Herald of your choice within 6&quot; of the slain model. The Herald may not charge on the turn of possession. If no eligible Psyker, count as The Warp is Calm.
12 — SUMMONED FROM THE WARP: A new unit of 2D6+3 Bloodletters, Pink Horrors, Plaguebearers, or Daemonettes (your choice) Deep Strikes onto the table.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="b2e4c6d3-0000-4000-8000-000000000030" name="Dreadskulls" hidden="false">
          <profiles/>
          <rules/>
          <infoLinks/>
          <modifiers/>
          <description>Place a marker next to each unit that takes one or more hits from this weapon. Any friendly Daemon unit that charges a unit so marked does not suffer the Initiative penalty when charging through difficult terrain. Remove Dreadskulls markers at the end of the Assault phase.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="b2e4c6d3-0000-4000-8000-000000000031" name="Gorefeast" hidden="false">
          <profiles/>
          <rules/>
          <infoLinks/>
          <modifiers/>
          <description>Whenever this model&apos;s Hammer of Wrath hits cause one or more unsaved Wounds in a single phase, roll a D6 — on a score of 4+, the model regains a single Structure Point spent earlier in the game.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="b2e4c6d3-0000-4000-8000-000000000032" name="Daemonic Resilience" hidden="false">
          <profiles/>
          <rules/>
          <infoLinks/>
          <modifiers/>
          <description>The model gains Daemonic Instability-style resistance: when this vehicle loses its last Structure Point, roll a D6. On a 6, the vehicle is not destroyed but is instead banished from the battlefield (removed as a casualty, but counts as a surviving unit for victory condition purposes involving unit counts).</description>
        </rule>
      </rules>
